    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-12-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="244"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d244">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/12–2754</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Secretary <persName corresp="#p_EDENSA1" type="from"
                            >Eden</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d244fn1">This message was delivered to <persName
                            corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Dulles</persName> by Ambassador <persName
                            corresp="#p_MAKINSRM1">Makins</persName> on Dec. 27. It was transmitted
                        to London for the information of the Ambassador in telegram 3378, Dec. 27,
                        which is the source text.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-12-27">December 27,
                            1954</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Dear <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Foster</persName>
                    </hi>:] If French vote goes wrong, we shall have to act great speed if we are to
                    hold position not only in Germany but also in other <gloss target="#t_WE1"
                        >WE</gloss> countries. You may like to have my preliminary thoughts now.</p>
                <p>It seems to me that immediate meeting will be necessary. In addition to us two
                    and Dr. <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1">Adenauer</persName> participants
                    should be representatives of <gloss target="#t_Benelux1">Benelux</gloss>, Italy
                    and Canada. In view Dr. <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1">Adenauer</persName>’s
                    age and health I think meeting should be held Europe. I should be happy to hold
                    it London. Failing that, the Hague, Rome or Brussels, but not Bonn, are
                    possibilities.</p>
                <p>I suggest that agenda should be: <list>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                        <item>Termination of occupation of <gloss target="#t_FedRep1"
                            >FedRep</gloss>;</item>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                        <item>German association with West and a German defence contribution;</item>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                        <item>Part to be played in new situation by <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                                >NATO</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_WE1">WE</gloss> Union.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">As at London Conference, Item (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) would
                    be for restricted UK/US/Ger discussion running parallel with Eight Power
                    discussion of other items.</p>
                <pb facs="0458" n="1526" xml:id="pg_1526"/>
                <p>I think there would be great advantage in preliminary meeting between you and me
                    immediately before main conference opens.</p>
                <p>[Kindest regards,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Anthony</hi>
                        </persName>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
